HEADWORD: Pettish
<hw>Pet"tish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Pet</er>.]</ety> <def>Fretful; peevish; moody; capricious; inclined
to ill temper.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>pettish</xex> kind of humor.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Sterne.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Pet"tish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pet"tish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

